
Intro
------------------------
a benchmark for dynamic script language performance which widely used in game development (simulate in a real product evironment)

The main structure of a game is usually a event driven loop.

The factor affect performance in a real online game include :
  1.  engine(C/C++) <---> VM call (script extend / embedded)
  2.  massive object create/destroy (Garbage Collection)
  3.  lots of function call
  4.  map(dict) / array manipulation
  5.  string manipulation (concat, split, slice, search, replace)

Run
---------------------------
  freebsd/Linux
  python 2.5 or above
  lua 5.1 or above
